OL,3,CGuernsey States told to introduce
OL,4,Cspeed cameras and penalty points
OL,6,FOther recommendations included
OL,7,Fstronger laws to tackle curb surfing
OL,8,Fand a points-based penalty system,
OL,9,Flike in the UK, which would build up
OL,10,Fon a person's record and potentially
OL,11,Fresult in driving sanctions.
OL,13,FDeputy Adrian Gabriel, Guernsey's
OL,14,FPresident of Environment and
OL,15,FInfrastructure, appeared to hint that
OL,16,Fmobile speed cameras would be
OL,17,Fconsidered over fixed ones.
OL,19,FHe says: "The trouble with a fixed
OL,20,Fcamera in a small community is that it
OL,21,Fcreates a bubble of conformity.
